The '''Pacific Islands ICT Policy and Strategic Plan''' was approved by [[Pacific Islands Forum]] leaders in 2000. The vision of the plan is '''Internet for Every Pacific Islander'''. This plan has been used as a template for developing national Information and Communication Technologies (ICT) policies in the [[Pacific Islands Forum]] countries. It has been also used for the [[World Summit on the Information Society]].<ref>http://www.forumsec.org/resources/uploads/attachments/documents/Pacific%20Islands%20ICT%20Policy%20and%20Strategic%20Plan%20(PIIPP)%202002.pdf</ref>
